Bolt Builds developed the staircase design concept for the TD Bank Center in Springfield, Connecticut, exploring how vertical circulation can become a strong architectural feature within a high-traffic public environment. The proposal reimagines the staircase as both a functional connector and a visual anchor within the larger interior.

The rendered design focuses on clean geometry, material cohesion, and clear sightlines to support spatial flow. Refined detailing, integrated handrails, and a restrained material palette were envisioned to elevate the experience of movement while responding to the scale of the surrounding area.

