rates how a thoughtfully designed staircase can contribute to the identity and clarity of a public space, turning circulation into a purposeful design moment. ","featuredImage":{"_key":null,"_type":"image","asset":{"_id":"image-762e8aff1af9d3cdeee29b38e1bf7dc114d5aa0b-2600x1441-png","_type":"sanity.imageAsset","description":null,"metadata":{"dimensions":{"aspectRatio":1.8043025676613462,"height":1441,"width":2600},"lqip":"data:image/png;base64,"},"tags":null},"caption":null,"crop":null},"images":[{"_key":"ff78e48fa03c","_type":"projectImage","asset":{"_id":"image-9f85dc8f82d5f0a40578dced1f1565c7a0ec7641-2600x1450-png","_type":"sanity.imageAsset","description":null,"metadata":{"dimensions":{"aspectRatio":1.793103448275862,"height":1450,"width":2600},"lqip":"data:image/png;base64,"},"tags":null},"caption":null,"crop":null},{"_key":"1a2eb7721def","_type":"projectImage","asset":{"_id":"image-32b5ed8dc82fa5e2ec10fa3476820bbb131a5398-2600x1446-png","_type":"sanity.imageAsset","description":null,"metadata":{"dimensions":{"aspectRatio":1.798063623789765,"height":1446,"width":2600},"lqip":"data:image/png;base64,"},"tags":null},"caption":null,"crop":null},{"_key":"0de3f7ac110e","_type":"projectImage","asset":{"_id":"image-762e8aff1af9d3cdeee29b38e1bf7dc114d5aa0b-2600x1441-png","_type":"sanity.imageAsset","description":null,"metadata":{"dimensions":{"aspectRatio":1.8043025676613462,"height":1441,"width":2600},"lqip":"data:image/png;base64,"},"tags":null},"caption":null,"crop":null}],"links":null,"location":"Springfield, Connecticut","role":"Design","services":[{"_id":"b2848913-e37f-47b4-aa20-f19f1ead3183","title":"Rendering"},{"_id":"9ebaf12d-1fa6-44bf-809d-0272d38653b4","title":"Interior Design"}],"size":"...","slug":"td-bank-center","tags":[{"_id":"2f164a14-e421-4e2f-bae1-60ed587fd51e","_type":"tag","slug":"commercial","title":"Commercial"}],"timeline":"3 months","title":"TD Bank Center "},"nextProject":{"_id":"ca8fb271-92dd-45d1-a17a-7e59d0f8854f","_type":"project","completedAt":"2026-01-01","description":[{"_key":"a74c06681024","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"8f0ce18d53fb0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Mimi's Froyo is a self-serve frozen yogurt concept built around a single organizing idea: every element of the space flows. Bolt Builds served as the design, build, and fabrication partner for the complete interior buildout, delivering a ground-up transformation of a narrow Manhattan storefront into one of the most spatially inventive retail interiors in the city."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"1fff2472f641","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"43ad0cfef9340","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"The project is defined by its geometry. A barrel-vaulted ceiling structure — clad entirely in white-oak veneer panels — sweeps from entry to back wall, collapsing the boundary between ceiling, arch, and millwork into a single continuous surface. The vault is not decorative; it's structural to the spatial concept, compressing and expanding the guest experience as they move through the space. The effect is part subway tunnel, part ocean liner — intimate, directional, and unmistakably original."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"c1b2e64a0ceb","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"5538e78d3c0f0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"At the heart of the design is a custom serpentine banquette, fabricated in-house by Bolt, that curves organically through the room. Its tufted cognac leather seating sits atop a plinth wrapped in hand-laid terracotta tile, creating a warm counterpoint to the stainless steel service counter and polished concrete floors. The counter itself — a flowing, sculptural form in brushed stainless — was custom-fabricated by Bolt to follow the curvature of the room, housing the brand's self-serve froyo machines in flush-mounted niches with custom aluminum surrounds."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"a89e7c8cae5c","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"c444f9edf05f0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"A back-lit glass block feature wall at the entry anchors the lounge zone, bathing the seating area in warm amber light and reinforcing the brand's retro-modern sensibility. Translucent ceiling panels diffuse light across the vault, eliminating harsh shadow and lending the service area a soft, luminous quality that photographs beautifully and makes the space feel larger than its footprint."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"ef984e624055","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"6891b85b50a70","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Bolt managed the project through every phase — schematic design, construction documentation, NYC DOB permitting, millwork fabrication, site construction, and final installation — with a single integrated team. No handoffs. No gaps. The result is a space where every curve, every material transition, and every detail is resolved with the precision that only full-scope design-build makes possible"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"}],"descriptionPlaintext":"Mimi's Froyo is a self-serve frozen yogurt concept built around a single organizing idea: every element of the space flows. Bolt Builds served as the design, build, and fabrication partner for the complete interior buildout, delivering a ground-up transformation of a narrow Manhattan storefront into one of the most spatially inventive retail interiors in the city.\n\nThe project is defined by its geometry. A barrel-vaulted ceiling structure — clad entirely in white-oak veneer panels — sweeps from entry to back wall, collapsing the boundary between ceiling, arch, and millwork into a single continuous surface. The vault is not decorative; it's structural to the spatial concept, compressing and expanding the guest experience as they move through the space. The effect is part subway tunnel, part ocean liner — intimate, directional, and unmistakably original.\n\nAt the heart of the design is a custom serpentine banquette, fabricated in-house by Bolt, that curves organically through the room. Its tufted cognac leather seating sits atop a plinth wrapped in hand-laid terracotta tile, creating a warm counterpoint to the stainless steel service counter and polished concrete floors. The counter itself — a flowing, sculptural form in brushed stainless — was custom-fabricated by Bolt to follow the curvature of the room, housing the brand's self-serve froyo machines in flush-mounted niches with custom aluminum surrounds.\n\nA back-lit glass block feature wall at the entry anchors the lounge zone, bathing the seating area in warm amber light and reinforcing the brand's retro-modern sensibility. Translucent ceiling panels diffuse light across the vault, eliminating harsh shadow and lending the service area a soft, luminous quality that photographs beautifully and makes the space feel larger than its footprint.\n\nBolt managed the project through every phase — schematic design, construction documentation, NYC DOB permitting, millwork fabrication, site construction, and final installation — with a single integrated team. No handoffs. No gaps. The result is a space where every curve, every material transition, and every detail is resolved with the precision that only full-scope design-build makes possible","featuredImage":{"_key":null,"_type":"image","asset":{"_id":"image-7b8d6be42c69a152f1f4b7c5d22f7e1a222556bb-1080x1350-png","_type":"sanity.imageAsset","description":null,"metadata":{"dimensions":{"aspectRatio":0.8,"height":1350,"width":1080},"lqip":"data:image/png;base64,"},"tags":null},"caption":null,"crop":null},"images":[{"_key":"a16ca73e283c","_type":"projectImage","asset":{"_id":"image-7b8d6be42c69a152f1f4b7c5d22f7e1a222556bb-1080x1350-png","_type":"sanity.imageAsset","description":null,"metadata":{"dimensions":{"aspectRatio":0.8,"height":1350,"width":1080},"lqip":"data:image/png;base64,"},"tags":null},"caption":null,"crop":null},{"_key":"64c777df7bea","_type":"projectImage","asset":{"_id":"image-0f5a367c7f2c3b3231af5c50ef3fe50c35dbb9f9-1920x1350-png","_type":"sani